<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-09-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-09-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="72" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 72.</note>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. E. B. Washburne</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Fish</persName>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[By cable telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-09-03"><hi rend="smallcaps">September</hi> 3,
                                    1870</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Fish,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi></p>
                        <p>McMahon totally defeated. Capture of Sedan. Defeat of Bazaine before
                            Metz. In Chamber Favre considered present government extinct<hi rend="italic">;</hi> proposed military dictator. Unofficial dispatch
                            to foreign minister that Emperor prisoner, another reports him escaped
                            to Belgium.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WASHBURNE.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>